image_desc: Photo by Smart Nation Singapore on February 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'TraceTogether helped to identify more than three-quarters quarters of the close contacts when a cruise passenger onboard the Royal Caribbean International's Quantum of the Seas initially tested positive for COVID-19 in December 2020. Identified by TraceTogether EJ 1 ...........'.
text:
Digital tools have helped to increase the speed and accuracy of contact tracing. The data provided by #SafeEntry (SE) and #TraceTogether (TT) are useful supplements used in parallel with manual contact tracing.

An example of TraceTogether’s role in contact tracing is demonstrated by the case on the Royal Caribbean International’s Quantum of the Seas in December 2020. When a cruise passenger initially tested positive on board the vessel, TT data helped to identify more than three-quarters of the close contacts.

Although the passenger subsequently tested negative, this incident demonstrates how TT can come into play when TT coverage is high. We need a high level of active participation in the TT Programme, so that we can identify close contacts quickly, and take the necessary actions for quarantine, and follow-up medical attention. So please be reminded to use your TraceTogether device (App or Token) actively by keeping your App in the background, and by bringing your Token with you when you leave home!

“所有要求调用个人接触者数据的申请，都得由警长（Inspector）提出，这和警方向金融机构要求提供银行数据的级别相同。”

只有高级警官才有权限申请调用防疫数据查案，所有申请也须得到刑事侦查局批准，内政部兼永续发展与环境部政务部长陈国明指出，政府为调用个人接触者追踪数据查案制定了充足的保障措施。

代表内政部答复多名议员提问的陈国明，在冠病（临时援助措施）（修正）法案昨天（2月2日）提出二读时，做出以上表示。他重申，警务人员申请调用防疫数据查案前须得到刑事侦查局批准，任何公务员如果为不属于七种重罪的调查工作泄露个人接触者追踪数据，都算触犯法律。根据相关规定，违例者将被罚款高达两万元或坐牢长达两年，或两者兼施，这比公共部门（治理）法令处以的高达5000元罚款及两年刑期更为严厉。

陈国明说，所有被调取的数据将加密及严格保密，只有得到授权的人员才能接触，当局也会详细记录接触数据的警员身份。🖼：早报制表

H Locations Visited Proximity Data User Information'.
text:
Earlier today, the Bill to introduce amendments in the COVID-19 (Temporary Measures) Act was moved in Parliament. This Bill will formalize the restrictions on the use of personal digital contact tracing data from Singapore’s national digital contact tracing systems.

The Bill makes clear that data from #TraceTogether, #SafeEntry and #Bluepass are to be used for contact tracing purposes only, the exception being investigations or criminal proceedings relating to specified serious offences. Safeguards are also set out in the legislation to provide further assurances to the public that the data is used for the appropriate purposes

政府将规定“合力追踪”和SafeEntry访客登记系统的数据在25天后自动清除，但若病毒变异或对病毒的了解加强，政府可根据医疗专家的建议更改该数据的保留期。

主管智慧国计划的外交部长维文医生今天在国会参与冠病（临时援助措施）（修正）法案二读辩论时指出，修正法案将要求部长指定无须再使用数码追踪系统来防止冠病疫情传播的日期，数据管理员之后须删除任何不需要的个人追踪数据。

“合力追踪”（TraceTogether）和SafeEntry数据目前已会在25天后自动清除，除非该数据已用于追踪病例密切接触者，或是有关严重罪行的调查或刑事诉讼。📸：林泽锐

text:
限制防疫数据使用方式的冠病（临时援助措施）（修正）法案，昨天（2月1日）以紧急方式提呈一读。国会今天（2日）复会时将对此进行辩论，法案三读通过后将于本月中旬生效。

根据修正法案内容，防疫数据将不受包括刑事诉讼法在内的其他成文法规约束，相关数据只有在追踪冠病病患接触者，或调查七种重罪时才准调用。这包括修正法案生效前收集的所有数据。内政部发言人答复询问时也说，警方人员调用这些数据查案前，须获得刑事侦查局批准。

此外，公务员或政府机构承包商在未经授权情况下使用或泄露个人接触者追踪数据，将被罚款高达2万元或坐牢长达两年，或两者兼施，这比公共部门（治理）法令处以的高达5000元罚款及两年刑期更为严厉。📸：SNDGG提供

text:
On behalf of the IVC Team over at Jurong,

Happy New Year!!

2020 has been tough for all, but we couldn’t have done it without you! Thank you for all the support and patience during this Pandemic.

Let’s usher in the new year with a clean slate and positivity!

We all still need to do our part to stop the spread and remain vigilant. We can do so by downloading the TraceTogether App, social distancing and wearing our masks at all times.

As of 1st January 2021, all clients are required to check in the safe entry via the TraceTogether App. Please approach our staff if you would like to check in via your Token or IC.

Although we’re at Phase 3, we are still required to minimise the number of people waiting outside the clinic. 

We do seek your cooperation to book your appointment before heading down and please ensure that only one owner is seated outside.

Let’s all do our part to keep Singapore safe and most importantly, a COVID free 2021!

Oh, and remember to keep away all unwanted treats/toys from your furry ones 😬

We hear you! Our officers are working hard with SG Digital Ambassadors and Safe Distancing Ambassadors from various agencies to engage premise owners so that the #TraceTogether Tokens can be used for SafeEntry check-ins at more places. This includes malls, eateries, supermarkets, hairdressing salons, beauty salons and more. You can look forward to more premises that will be TraceTogether-ready in the coming weeks.

Don’t worry if you haven’t had a chance to collect your Token. The use of the TraceTogether App or Token to check in for SafeEntry will not be mandatory yet. So while Token-scanning will become more widely available, you are still able to scan QR codes with your phone’s camera or #SingPass Mobile, or use your ID for check-in till further notice.

text:
Is the #TraceTogether Token ‘intrinsically safe’? Can I bring the Token into a petrol station? 😰

Rest assured that the Token is safe for general daily use! 👍🏻

The term ‘intrinsic safety’ or ‘IS’ is a technical design approach for equipment that is often carried into hazardous areas by limiting the energy level available to cause an ignition. The electronic devices that we use daily like our handphones, laptops, and headphones are generally not IS-certified.

Use TraceTogether today to join us as an ally to protect our loved ones and enter Phase 3 safely! 

TraceTogether, Safer Together.🛡️

image_desc: Photo by Mind the Gab on December 29, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'THE GAB Injustice Served with Side Chicken Metaphors OfChicken Wingsa and Whole Chickens: Dissecting the Fortitude Budget" witter(Truth?) Trump. The Rap Race Continues 2 MAY I 2020'.
text:
Issue 2 • May 31, 2020⁣
⁣
The coronavirus is pretty much under control at this moment in Singapore - and indeed, as we’ve seen in the past year, that’s no simple feat! But the image of the city-state being the gold standard in virus tracing was shattered in April, when there was a sudden surge in cases in migrant worker dormitories (it is now trying to reclaim this narrative through #tracetogether). ⁣
⁣
In May, the world also watched George Floyd breathe his last through our screens, under the knee of a police officer (as other police officers watched on), who represented the long history of policing in America that has roots in slave patrols. We mourned together, were spurred to anger by the injustice we witnessed, and called for reforms for the policing system.⁣
⁣
Therefore, this issue of the newsletter sheds light on the concurrent pandemics of inequality and racism in Singapore and America. It focuses on the systemic injustices perpetuated by the input-intensive economic growth model in Singapore and includes some mixed media reflections on race and racism in response to the racially-charged incidents in America. ⁣
⁣
As both countries conclude important elections this year, it’s worth a re-read as we continue to hold our newly elected representatives accountable in addressing these systemic problems that have been brought to light.

text:
我国已达到七成国人加入“合力追踪”计划的目标，全国所有民众俱乐部也已分批开放让人领取携手防疫器。政府下来计划重新启动那些已暂停分发防疫器的民众俱乐部，并通过学校分发防疫器给学生。

主管智慧国计划的外交部长维文医生昨早走访甘榜景万岸民众俱乐部并在受访时透露，截至本月21日，已有超过205万名用户下载及注册使用“合力追踪”（TraceTogether）应用，以及超过175万个携手防疫器被领取。

为了应付需求，政府已订购更多防疫器，到了明年2月底，预计共生产500万个，足以让所有需要的居民领取。公众会在民众俱乐部重新开放领取防疫器的至少三天前获得通知，他们也可通过TokenGoWhere网站，或社区布告栏查看最新消息。📸：饶进礼

image_desc: Photo by Vivian Balakrishnan on December 22, 2020. May be an image of 1 person and sitting.
text:
#TraceTogether may be the world’s most successful digital contact tracing programme. We have surpassed the 70% participation rate in Singapore. Thank you all for your trust, confidence and support!⠀
⠀
I visited Kampong Kembangan CC, one of the final 6 CCs to commence Token distribution. To date, over 1.75 million Tokens have been distributed across the island. By end Feb 2021, 5 million Tokens would have been produced, so please be assured that everyone will get a chance to collect one. You do not need to collect a token if you have already downloaded the App, as both serve the same function.⠀
 ⠀
GovTech (Government Technology Agency of Singapore) is currently prototyping a device so that we can operate a familiar ‘TAP-AND-GO’ check-in system similar to EZ Link gantries. This will make the process even more convenient and quick in the future.⠀
 ⠀
As we reflect on a challenging and unforgettable year, let’s continue to do our part to keep everyone safe and sound.

text:
Introducing the challenges for Phase C

❇️ Base Challenge
Worth: 25 POINTS
Task: Take a picture of yourself at any of the parks marked on our Walking the Mile map.
Bonus points: Picture of yourself at a Mosque (+ 20 points)

✴️ Featured Challenge
Worth: 100 POINTS

Task: Take out a camera and start creating a reflection video about your journey with Walking the Mile! 

Film your video and send it to us via the StepsTracker Link! If the file exceeds the limit, upload your video to youtube and send us the link. 

Here are some guiding questions to help you craft your reflection:

- How do you feel about keeping active?
- What have you learnt from the Hijrah values?
- How can you apply the Hijrah values in your daily life?
- What are some challenges you encounter during your journey?
- What do we need to be cautious of while Walking the Mile?

You must submit all challenges through the StepTracker form. Once our team has verified your entries, your points will be credited under your UniqueID within 2-3 days.

Details of submission of Challenge Entries can be found in our manual. Refer to the link in bio for any other information.

Remember to always follow the existing rules, regulations and guidelines. 🤓
And as always, take care, stay safe and have fun! #tracetogether

image_desc: Photo by apollos michio | bookstagram in 2020 with @marshallcavendish, @ekocoon, and @cheong.felix. May be an image of book.
text:
[Book 97 of 2020] In the Year of the Virus is a very short book that accompanies poems by local author Felix Cheong with beautiful illustrations by illustrator Eko. These poems are all related to Covid-19 in one way or another and capture the widespread emotions and feelings we have regarding this life-changing pandemic.
.
Although the book is really short and can be read in literally less than five minutes, it is a book that can be revisited and pondered upon over time. I enjoyed reading and interpreting the author’s poems in my own way and looking at the evocative illustrations. A meaningful and retrospective read!
.
Rating: 4/5
.

QR code is an abbreviation of "Quick Response Code.” While this may sound a little abstract, in Chinese, QR code is 二维码(èr wéi mǎ), literally "two-dimensional barcode". Do you find it much easier to understand now?🤩

image_desc: Photo by Trev@ | Travel App on December 14, 2020. May be an image of buildings and skyscraper.
text:
Great news! From Dec 18, Singapore will lift border restrictions for visitors from Taiwan!!⁠
⁠
Of course, with the border slowly opening up, there are still rules and regulations to follow to keep us all safe!⁠
⁠
1. Travellers can apply to enter Singapore from next Friday, if they have been in Taiwan for the last 14 days straight before departure.⁠
⁠
2. Upon arrival, visitors will undergo a COVID-19 PCR test! If the result is negative, they will be allowed to go about their activities in Singapore without serving a stay-home notice.⁠
⁠
3. Travellers from Taiwan must download and register for the TraceTogether app on their mobile devices before entering Singapore and keep it activated during their stay!⁠
⁠
4. They must not delete it for 14 consecutive days after leaving Singapore. ⁠
⁠
5. They will be responsible for their medical bills related to COVID-19 while in Singapore.⁠
⁠
Now with all these safety measures, we must still do our part and be vigilant so we can all start to travel again!⁠
⁠

text:
目前使用“合力追踪”应用和携手防疫器的公众已达到约65%，加上政府有能力每天进行超过5万次的聚合酶链式反应检测，政府因此认为新加坡已达到进入第三阶段的条件。

我国抗疫跨部门工作小组表示，政府会给予国人更多时间领取取携手防疫器，明年初才执行强制使用“合力追踪”进行SafeEntry登记的措施。

在这项新措施实施之前，公众仍可以通过电子政府密码应用（SingPass Mobile）、扫描QR码或身份证件等不同方式完成SafeEntry登记。

工作小组今天在记者会上说，过去几个月来，大家合力达到了这些要求：
👉 截至昨天，已有约65%本地居民使用合力追踪应用和携手防疫器，应能在今年底达到早前设下的70％目标。

👉 当局现每天能完成超过5万次的聚合酶链式反应（Polymerase Chain Reaction，简称PCR）检测，而且也在举行较大型和高风险的活动时，为参与者进行抗原快速检测。

👉 多数商家和公众都极力配合安全管理措施，让社区传播病例维持在低水平。📸：档案照

Wondering why your #TraceTogether App shows Bluetooth exchanges when you’re home alone or when there’s no one beside you? Is your app faulty? 😳

📲 It’s not an error with your app! Bluetooth's range is about 10 metres (and could be more), so TraceTogether Apps and Tokens within this distance (such as your neighbours’) could still exchange signals with your phone.

The information is processed and filtered based on duration and signal strength to identify close contacts. The number of Bluetooth exchanges is only an estimate! 

Use TraceTogether today to join us as an ally in keeping our nation protected and helping us reopen safely!

TraceTogether, Safer Together.🛡️

image_desc: Photo by Nadine Bogatenkova on December 04, 2020.
text:
Про круизный лайнер #quantumoftheseas 🚢
Оказалось,  что именно этот лайнер - первый в компании #royalcaribbean  во всем мире, который был запущен после пандемии.
Хотя у лайнера багамская юрисдикция, на борту действуют все те же сингапурские правила, то есть нельзя собираться группами более пяти человек, обязательно носить  маски, соблюдение социальной дистанции. К этому ещё добавилось ношение специального браслета во все время нахождения в круизе, наличие специального установленного приложения на телефоне #tracetogether , а также , карточки которую надо сканировать при входе/выходе  в любое помещения корабля. 
На входе в рестораны также замеряют температуру, а ещё приходят утром прямо в каюту для замера. Все строго, в 10:30 спиртное не продают. Говорят, что правительство отправило несколько человек на борт, чтобы следить за порядком, и от соблюдения всех этих жёстких правил зависит будут ли продолжать такие поездки.

Загрузка лайнера сейчас  30 % , при этом, на 1200 клиентов приходится столько же членов экипажа. Состав команд интернациональный- филиппинцы, индусы, индонезийцы, украинцы. И даже не знаю, кто больше рад, команда или гости, что плаванье возобновили. 

На борту длиной 350 метров и шириной 40 метров неимоверное количество развлечений - аэротруба #ifly , мини-картинг , серф симулятор, пара бассейнов, и даже такая штука, которая подымает тебя на высоту 100 метров над морем.. #northstar
Несколько театров, концертных площадок, обилие ресторанов (есть даже именитые шефы)! А с высоты сегодня я разглядела беговой трек вокруг палубы. 

Как опыт, классная история, хоть и плывем мы по маршруту Сингапур-Сингапур. Но в нормальной жизни, круизный формат - не моя история.  Я за природу, спонтанность и прогулки без маршрутов. ☺️🤗

#сингапур #круиз #royalcarribeancruise  #royalcaribbeansingapore #cruisetonowhere

image_desc: Photo by 早报 zaobao.sg on November 29, 2020. May be an image of one or more people and screen.
text:
配合年底佳节的许多活动，本地多个宗教场所与机构都打算申请将现场活动人数上限调高至250人，意味着不下载“合力追踪”应用或领取携手防疫器的信众，可能无法出席这些活动。

政府早前宣布，更多公共场所将只接受使用“合力追踪”的公众。换言之，要进入这些场所，要么须下载“合力追踪”应用以扫描SafeEntry的QR码，要么得携带携手防疫器（token）。卫生部长颜金勇之前在国会回答询问时也说，使用“合力追踪”让政府更有信心放宽大型活动、宗教场所和现场表演的人数限制，例如试行举办最多250人的商业活动。

受访的宗教场所，有的已经全面实施要求信众使用“合力追踪”应用或携手防疫器入场，过程顺畅；有的则表示由于信众多是年长者，实施安全管理措施时难免会遇到问题，不过，他们将持续与信众沟通，确保顺利过渡。📸：受访者提供

I've detached the lanyard that comes with it so as to just keep in my pocket and not hang around my neck like a necklace.

image_desc: Photo by apollos michio | bookstagram in Singapore. May be an image of book and text that says 'DIARY Tales of Panic Buying, AFORMER RMER COVIDIOT and Finding Humour Surviving during the Coronavirus Pandemic Christina Thé'.
text:
[Book 91 of 2020] Diary of a Former Covidiot is a really relatable book that depicts the funny ways in which we have adapted to the Circuit Breaker life since the unbidden invasion of Covid-19.
.
From wearing masks, to Zoom-ing, to rationing toilet paper and suddenly becoming runners at the parks nearby, Christina Thé comments on her observations of herself and those around her during this period of unprecedented duress and stress.
.
Although I find some—actually maybe just one—of her sweeping statements rather offensive (even if they are meant to be jokes), and fail to fully relate to her life as a single mother raising two daughters, this is still a funny book that records the virus-ridden 2020 in a humorous way.
.
Rating: 3.5/5
.

P.S. As part of the National Reading Movement’s #3x3BookClub (see @readingnationsg), I’ll recommend two others books: Educated by Tara Westover and My Dark Vanessa by Kate Elizabeth Russell! + No-obligations tag for @opportunereads, @twentycharm and @yatzerooni! You can stand a chance to win GrabFood vouchers worth $50! 😆
.

image_desc: Photo by Masjid Darul Ghufran on November 26, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'SafeEntry TraceTogether Mengapa kita perlukan kedua-duanya? 503 TAMPINES AVE SINGAPURA 529651 TEL: 6786 5545 WW.DARULGHUFRAN. MASJID DARUL GHUFRAN DARULGHUFRAN'.
text:
Assalamualaikum semua
.
Mengapa kita memerlukan kedua-dua SafeEntry dan TraceTogether untuk menyokong usaha pengesanan kontak di Singapura?
.
Dengan alat digital seperti SafeEntry dan TraceTogether, purata jangka masa untuk pengesanan kontak dipercepatkan dari 4 hari ke kurang daripada 2 hari.
Pengesanan kontak yang lebih cepat membenarkan kita meneruskan aktiviti biasa dengan lebih yakin.
.
Antara yang kita boleh lakukan untuk melindungi diri dan masjid-masjid kita adalah seperti berikut:
.
Memuat turun aplikasi mudah alih TraceTogether di https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg/
.
Dapatkan token TraceTogether (https://token.gowhere.gov.sg/) dan bawa bersama anda ketika datang ke masjid-masjid.
.
Anda juga boleh mendapatkan bantuan pegawai masjid di 24 masjid-masjid yang menerima kemasukan melalui TraceTogether Safe Entry.
.
Bersama kita boleh membantu komuniti dan negara kita dalam mengekang penularan pandemik ini, Insya Allah.
.

image_desc: Photo by Dream Squad on November 25, 2020. May be an image of 1 person, screen and text that says 'DREAM SPUAD UAD WEDEVELOF COVID-19 Technology and Gamification to Fight Covid-19!'.
text:
Despite the prevailing Covid-19 situation, most of the nations are taking actions to move forward in this cumbersome time period keeping the countries away from total lockdowns. When it comes to economics, countries and their governments struggle really hard to shield the economic collapse at a time which the countries are not fully operated.

But technology has developed to a great extent, which has the ability to curb the spread of Covid-19. While, number of researches are being conducted to find the best ways to get the aid of gamification and technology to fight against and control the spread of the pandemic.

There are two types approaches which we can use technology to encourage the prevention of Coronavirus. Proactive technology supports actions control the spread like, social distancing and washing hands. Reactive technology, focuses on actions to be taken at the occurrence of risk incidents.

In China’s Health Code App, it displays a colored badge for each individual which reflects his/her health status. Green says that you’re free to travel outside and if it’s Yellow or Red you have to alert authorities. Apart from the effectiveness of this method, there are certain concerns on app’s transparency and data collection.

Singapore launched the TraceTogether App which works via Bluetooth and enables to track the engagements between users. All the data is stored in the mobile phones of the users. At a Covid positive instance, the government requests the access to the data attached to the app for contact tracing. 

When it comes to maintaining social distancing, an app could provide a score for how well the user maintained social distancing. While the app can remind users to wash their hands every two hours, use sanitizer after using public transportation. 

Technology and gamification lead people to filter their top priorities from unnecessary outings and it will help people to lower the number of contacts they will get.

Don’t want to use #TraceTogether because you don’t want to be tracked? 😳

We’ve got good news for you!

The TraceTogether App and Token do not collect any location data and there is no way for the government to locate your real-time whereabouts with this app. Both only perform Bluetooth exchanges between TraceTogether devices. 

The logs stay in your devices and will never be accessed by the Ministry of Health without your consent. The only time would be when you have been confirmed as a COVID-19 patient or were deemed to be in close contact with one. 

Use TraceTogether today to join us as an ally in keeping our nation protected and helping us re-open safely! Remember to keep your app updated to the latest version and complete your profile registration if you haven’t already done so. 

TraceTogether, Safer Together.🛡️

#TechForPublicGood #GovTechSG #SGUnited

text:
The Community Clubs in #Sembawang GRC will begin the #TraceTogether token collection on Thursday, 26 November 2020 and Friday, 27 November 2020.

Remember: if we have downloaded the TraceTogether App, we actually don’t need the tokens.

Try let those who don’t use the TraceTogether App to collect the tokens first - such as the elderly and those without handphones. 

The collection will go on for at least two weeks, so there's plenty of time.

We have made arrangements such that you can go to your nearest CC to collect the tokens, even if the CC is in another Division served by a different MP. 

So if you live in block 301 and is part of Sembawang Central Division under me, you can collect the tokens at Canberra CC near your home, even though the CC is in Canberra Division under Dr @limweekiak.

Check out the schedule of collection here.

image_desc: Photo by Superstar Teacher SG on November 20, 2020. May be an image of 1 person, child, hair and text that says 'TraceTogether will only be effective for Students when all tokens are given out. superstar teacher'.
text:
Has your child collected his or her TraceTogether token yet? As we transition towards the use of the TraceTogether app or token for SafeEntry, MOE has recently announced that the use of TraceTogether in schools will take place gradually in December this year until all tokens have been given out. Students are encouraged to use the token instead of the app as they may not have access to their mobile devices at all times.

To find out where you can collect the tokens, just head on to https://token.gowhere.gov.sg/.

A 70% participation rate in the TraceTogether programme is one of the conditions for Phase 3 of re-opening, so let us all keep ourselves safe and work together to help Singapore achieve that.

With TraceTogether, contact tracers will be able to link and notify us quickly if we had possible exposure to confirmed Covid-19 cases. So, the earlier we are alerted and able to take action, the better we can protect ourselves, our loved ones and the community.

To get TraceTogether, go to tracetogether.gov.sg to download the app or you can also collect the TraceTogether token at your area. To check if your area has started the distribution of TraceTogether token, simply go to token.gowhere.gov.sg.

text:
Totally insane, y’all... I’ve been out of the house for only 3 hours!
.
1,549 total exchanges thus far and the day is not even halfway thru yet. Imagine what the count will look like at 6pm?! 😱
.
Click on the “See details” (or “history”) and it will list the places you’ve checked-in via SafeEntry over the last 14 days... it’s like those FB thingy that you proudly tell the world where you’re at when shopping for that $3,000 wallet or sipping that $30 a pot black tea 😉😜. It’s not a tracking, but a tracing. 
.
So, really no concern about your privacy being violated unless you fear your spouse/partner/mom/dad check your 14-day history and found out about your sinful activities. 🤦🏻‍♂️😂🤣
.
Here’s the thing, y’all. We know COVID-19 is a highly aggressive invasion and we need all the help we can get to defeat it. Time is the essence in this fight and tracing tools such as this app (or device) will expedite the contact tracing process in the event someone in our close proximity is infected. Think of it as you signing in the guest book at your friend’s wedding... you want your friend to know that you were there to celebrate with him/her that joyous occasion. 😉
.
It’s just genius that the SafeEntry is also cleverly integrated into TraceTogether to lessen further inconvenience. If you asked me... this is a killer app, technology at its best!
.
.
.
#blessedlife #lifestyle #grateful #lifepriorities #tracetogether #safeentry #covid_19 #covid #coronavirus

text:
Assalamualaikum everyone
.
Why do we need both SafeEntry and TraceTogether to support Singapore’s contract tracing efforts?
.
With digital tools like SafeEntry and TraceTogether, the average time for contact tracing has beed reduced from 4 days to less than 2 days.
Quicker contact tracing allows us to resume normal activities with greater confidence.
.
Here is what we can do to help keep ourselves and our mosques safe:
.
Download the TraceTogether app at https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg/
.
Collect your individual TraceTogether Token (https://token.gowhere.gov.sg/) and always carry it when visiting the mosques.
.
In addition, you can also seek assistance from mosque officials when you visit any of the 24 mosques accepting TraceTogether Safe Entry check-ins.
.
Together we can help the community and the nation to battle the spread of this pandemic, Insya Allah.
.

text: Participating in the #TraceTogether Programme is important, whether you test positive for Covid-19, or have come into contact with a Covid+ case. As a patient, you would want people you were in close contact with to be notified and taken care of; and as a close contact, you would want to be notified quickly to take the necessary next steps. Everyone has a part to play in contact tracing. Together we can help reduce the risk of new transmission chains forming. Take part in community contact tracing by using the App or Token today. Visit www.tracetogether.gov.sg for more info.

image_desc: Photo by K’s aviation (3.8K) in Hong Kong International Airport 香港國際機場.
text:
#新加坡共和國 將會與 #香港特別行政區 合作推行航空旅遊氣泡，於推行初期時每日只會有一來回航班，每航班只承載200人。

#剷屎官小編 知道香港人旅遊心切而外界安排信息比較亂， 加上香港國際機場 (HKG) 的入境層已經準備航空旅遊氣泡所需工具，故可以確實新加坡共和國及香港特別行政區兩地的安排。

旅客進入 #新加坡 共和國是不需要進行檢查，但任何國籍人仕必須在過去 14 天無到過新加坡共和國及香港特別行政區以外的國家及地區 (含中國及澳門特別行政區) ，並需要於出發前72小時內進行聚合酶連鎖反應檢查 (咽喉拭子/鼻腔拭子皆可) 及呈陰性結果，就會符合毋須履行居家通知之條件。 

另外旅客需要於抵達新加坡共和國前之72小時內填寫及遞交新加坡電子入境卡 (SG Arrival Card)，由於新加坡入境卡 (俗稱白卡) 早已於往年被電子化並普及化，故需要於 #AppStore 或 #GooglePlay 下載。

填寫資料與以往大同小異，包括英文護照全名、性別、出生日期、出生地、國籍 (因為新加坡共和國無香港籍緣故， 故持特區護照者需要選擇CHINESE，而英國國民海外護照則選擇BRITISH NATIONAL OVERSEAS)、護照號碼及到期日、護照辦理地、電話、電郵。

不過並未完成，因為之後需要於網上向新加坡移民與關卡局 (ICA SG) 申情Air Travel Pass，入境時需要下載 #TraceTogether 並於新加坡共和國境內使用。用者需要於TraceTogether申報入境種類、英文全名、性別、護照資料等，之後基於使用藍牙與新加坡居民交換信號及紀錄，故入境後不能關閉手提電話藍牙。而新加坡長期准證持有者，除遞交外遊史、檢測和遞交電子入境卡外，長期准證持有者亦須獲得新加坡相關當局的入境許可，否則可能會被拒絕入境。

相對新加坡共和國，香港特別行政區入境文書手續較少，但會再作一次即場檢查。任何人士包括持有新加坡人力部發出的工作准證(WP)或 S准證(SP) 外國護照持有人 (從事建築業、海事船廠業或加工業人士除外) 不論國籍，在過去 14 天無到過新加坡共和國或香港特別行政區以外的國家，並需要於出發前72小時內進行聚合酶連鎖反應檢查 (咽喉拭子/鼻腔拭子皆可) 及呈陰性結果，以及符合一般的簽證及入境規定，即可以乘搭航空旅遊氣泡的專屬航班前往香港。

所有航空旅遊氣泡的旅客在辦理登機手續時需要出示香港衞生署的電子健康申報表並生成QR碼、由新加坡政府指定之診所或檢測中心或香港特區政府認可的醫療檢測機構所發出之聚合酶連鎖反應檢查。

在新加坡共和國接受聚合酶連鎖反應檢查必須向新加坡移民與關卡局 (ICA SG) 預先提出申請，成功申請者會於提出申請後三個工作天內獲得通知。申請獲批後旅客可以預約到其中一間指定診所或檢測中心接受聚合酶連鎖反應檢查，檢測樣本如前所述必須在航班的預定起飛時間前 72 小時內採集。檢測報告須載有接受檢測的人士的姓名(須與有效旅遊證件所示姓名相同)及進行檢測的機構名稱，並列明對該樣本進行的檢測結果呈陰性、採集樣本的日期和時間以及抵港檢測服務預約。 

任何乘客抵港後都需要於圖中位置進行強制檢測，首先需要接受體溫檢查及出示電子健康申報結果，所有航空旅遊氣泡的旅客必須在出發前預約檢驗並生成QR碼，抵港後出示檢測預約證明QR碼、出示護照及登記領取樣本包，嬰兒方面需要提供糞便樣本以供檢測，收集樣本後將樣本袋交予收集處。完成所有程序後前往入境大堂辦理一般入境手續，入境後於指定地點等候檢驗結果及領取行李。檢驗基本收費為每人499港元，旅客可以為同行的人士一併預約並繳費。 

換言之除非快閃遊，否則由獲得結果到登機返回原居地前總時限超過72小時的話，就必須再於當地重做一次聚合酶連鎖反應檢查。另外返港後也需要與香港特區政府再繳付多一筆檢查費及交DNA予衛生署，所以需要正視細節。
location: Hong Kong International Airport 香港國際機場

image_desc: Photo by Smart Nation Singapore on November 12, 2020. May be an image of text that says '......... ......... TraceTogether data can only be decrypted by moH. raceTogether logs are stored in user's devices and will only be retrieved when a user tests positive for Covid-19.'.
text:
We are committed to safeguarding your privacy. The logs of #TraceTogether Bluetooth exchanges stay in your phone or token. When you test positive for Covid-19, MOH will seek your consent to share the logs with them. The data is also encrypted and can only be decrypted with MOH’s privately-held key.

Let's do our part for contact tracing and download the TraceTogether App today. Visit https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg for more info.

Note: This post was updated on 6 Jan 2021 following clarification on the usage of TraceTogether data in Parliament on 5 Jan 2021.

text:
Assalamualaikum semua
.
Sudahkah anda memuat turun TraceTogether hari ini?
.
Mari kita belajar untuk menggunakan TraceTogether, dan bersama melindungi orang-orang yang tersayang. Mari mainkan peranan dalam mengawal penularan COVID-19 melalui usaha sama pengesanan hubungan.
.
Antara yang kita boleh lakukan untuk melindungi diri dan masjid-masjid kita adalah seperti berikut:
.
Memuat turun aplikasi mudah alih TraceTogether di https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg/
.
Dapatkan token TraceTogether (https://token.gowhere.gov.sg/) dan bawa bersama anda ketika datang ke masjid-masjid.
.
Anda juga boleh mendapatkan bantuan pegawai masjid di 24 masjid-masjid yang menerima kemasukan melalui TraceTogether Safe Entry.
.
Bersama kita boleh membantu komuniti dan negara kita dalam mengekang penularan pandemik ini, Insya Allah.
.

image_desc: Photo by Smart Nation Singapore on November 08, 2020. May be an image of one or more people, hair and text that says 'TWO-IN-ONE! ONE APP FOR TWO CONTACT TRACING NEEDS Download the TraceTogether App today!'.
text:
Both #SafeEntry and #TraceTogether help to increase the speed and accuracy of MOH's contact tracing efforts, and are equally important.
 
The TraceTogether App serves two contact tracing needs. First, it allows you to perform SafeEntry check-ins. This helps to generate an activity map should you test positive for Covid-19. It also helps jog your memory when trying to recall where you have been over a period of time. Second, the app itself helps MOH to identify who you were in close proximity with, through the record of Bluetooth exchanges between devices.
 
Let's do our part for contact tracing and download the TraceTogether App today. Visit https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg for more info.

image_desc: Photo by Cornerstone Community Church on November 02, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'Starting 14-15 Nov 2020, check-in for our services will only be via n TraceTogether'.
text:
𝗧𝗥𝗔𝗖𝗘𝗧𝗢𝗚𝗘𝗧𝗛𝗘𝗥 𝗦𝗬𝗦𝗧𝗘𝗠 𝗦𝗧𝗔𝗥𝗧𝗜𝗡𝗚 𝟭𝟰-𝟭𝟱 𝗡𝗢𝗩 

Hey Church! We've been selected as one of the churches to pilot 250 pax per service. In the coming weeks, we’ll be gradually increasing our congregation capacity from our present 100pax to 250 per service. For this to happen, we’ll need to implement and utilise the TraceTogether App as our only Safe Entry system. This is in-line with the Government's latest advisory for the use of the Trace Together system, which will be implemented across the nation in December. 
 
So starting 14 & 15 Nov. check-in for all our services will only be done via the 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗰𝗲𝗧𝗼𝗴𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝗮𝗽𝗽 or by showing your 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗰𝗲𝗧𝗼𝗴𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝘁𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻𝘀. Singpass, Safe Entry QR Code scanning or presenting of NRIC will no longer be accepted as check-in options then.
 
𝟭. 𝗗𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗹𝗼𝗮𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗰𝗲𝗧𝗼𝗴𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝗔𝗽𝗽 by scanning the QR code or go to tracetogether.gov.sg. 
Should you need assistance, approach our Info Central at the end of service, call the church office or visit the TraceTogether website for more info.

𝟮. 𝗖𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗧𝗿𝗮𝗰𝗲𝗧𝗼𝗴𝗲𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿 𝗧𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻 – To find out where the collection point for your TraceTogether token is, go to https://token.gowhere.gov.sg

text:
So I got a little bit too excited when I realised the airpod cosies I made previously fit the TraceTogether tokens that the government is giving out. 

But look at these cuties!
I had to make some tweaks so you can just push up the top to scan the code but they turned really nice if I may say so myself. I mean if we are going to carry around these tokens, might as well have some fun with them right? And I don't mean tampering with them in some illegal way, I mean dressing them up and differentiating yours from others! 

I was quite appalled when I saw very similar airpod cosies on Etsy selling for $30 to $50 USD, read USD$. 

Yes handmade items are time consuming and require a lot of work, but I do what I do because I love doing it and it makes me happy! Don't worry, nothing over SGD$30 here! I value my work but I'm not out to commit daylight robbery. 🤣

For me, I'm happy when you're happy with your orders! I'm about halfway adding these to the store so do check them out! And as always, thank you for your support especially in such trying times. Happy Sunday loves!

text:
What’s the difference between SafeEntry and TraceTogether? SafeEntry helps to identify the places that COVID-19 cases have been to so that MOH can spot potential clusters. Whereas TraceTogether helps MOH identify people who were in close contact with COVID-19 cases during the infectious period. These two digital tools work together to increase the speed and accuracy of MOH's contact tracing efforts.

Even though the number of COVID-19 cases within our community remains low, we still have to vigilant! Let's do our part by making sure we are actively using #TraceTogether and #SafeEntry. 

You can now perform SafeEntry check-ins and check your possible exposure to Covid-19 at the same time. Help keep Singapore safe - download the TraceTogether App today!

Visit https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg for more info.

Muat turun aplikasi pengesanan hubungan1 ini untuk membolehkan pengesanan dan pengasingan kes COVID-1 dengan lebih pantas demi mengawal penularan virus. Jika dimaklum lebih awal, tindakan pantas dapat diambil bagi melindungi diri serta orang tersayang dengan lebih baik 503 TAMPINES AVE SINGAPURA 529651 TEL: 6786 5545 WWW.DARULGHUFRAN.OR MASJID DARUL GHUFRAN DARULGHUFRAN'.
text:
Assalamualaikum semua
.
Sudahkah anda memuat turun TraceTogether hari ini?
.
Mari kita belajar untuk menggunakan TraceTogether, dan bersama melindungi orang-orang yang tersayang. Mari mainkan peranan dalam mengawal penularan COVID-19 melalui usaha sama pengesanan hubungan.
.
Antara yang kita boleh lakukan untuk melindungi diri dan masjid-masjid kita adalah seperti berikut:
.
Memuat turun aplikasi mudah alih TraceTogether di https://www.tracetogether.gov.sg/
.
Dapatkan token TraceTogether (https://token.gowhere.gov.sg/) dan bawa bersama anda ketika datang ke masjid-masjid.
.
Anda juga boleh mendapatkan bantuan pegawai masjid di 24 masjid-masjid yang menerima kemasukan melalui TraceTogether Safe Entry.
.
Bersama kita boleh membantu komuniti dan negara kita dalam mengekang penularan pandemik ini, Insya Allah.

image_desc: Photo by 早报 zaobao.sg on October 26, 2020. May be an image of one or more people and people standing.
text:
派发携手防疫器的民众俱乐部近日出现人龙，主管智慧国计划的外交部长维文医生承诺，只有在所有国人都有合力追踪手机应用或携手防疫器后，才会落实以应用或防疫器登记进入商场的规定。他也强调，政府目前计划制造超过270万个防疫器，并有能力增加，不会出现供不应求的情况，公众无须窝蜂赶去领取。

维文医生昨天（10月25日）傍晚到波娜维斯达民众俱乐部视察派发防疫器的工作，除了对公众的支持表示感激，也大派定心丸。他说，当局正探讨在必要时增加防疫器的派发点。全国目前有38个民众俱乐部开放让公众领取防疫器，到了下个月，所有108个俱乐部都会是派发点。当局也考虑之后将防疫器分发给入境本地的旅客。

维文强调，本地社区传播病例虽然不高，但国人不可掉以轻心，而追踪曾接触病患者仍是防止病毒扩散的关键。📸 ：陈斌勤

To move safely into Phase 3, the Singapore Government has advised that we need: 

😷 Small group sizes, safe distancing, social responsibility

📱 Higher adoption of TraceTogether (TT)
- For quick contact tracing as group sizes increase
- Download the app or collect the token at token.gowhere.gov.sg

🦠 Pre-event Covid-19 testing
- For larger-scale & higher-risk activities
- Participants to be tested before events
- Trials at B2B events, wedding receptions etc

✔️ What to expect in Phase 3:
- 8-person gatherings (up from current 5)
- Multiple zones of 50 pax for events
- More travel to resume

❌ Certain high risk activities may not resume:
- E.g. bars, pubs, karaoke lounges & nightclubs
- Exploring limited pilots for this industry to resume safely

More: go.gov.sg/roadmap-to-phase3

text:
🤔 What comes to mind when you think of the word ‘token’? Would it be the arcade or the #TraceTogether Token which we use for contact tracing? 

In the world of programming, a ‘token’ refers to a single element in a programming language that enables a function to be performed — just like how the TraceTogether Token enables us to be safe and accounted for! 

As Singapore prepares to enter Phase 3, we need more people to get onboard the TraceTogether programme for us to resume normal activities with greater confidence.

Visit token.gowhere.gov.sg to find out where/when you can collect your TraceTogether Token (Note: Only for those who prefers to carry along a Token vs keeping the TraceTogether App running!). 

TraceTogether, safer together.

#TechTalk #GovTechSG

image_desc: Photo by TODAY on October 21, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'TraceTogether MINISTRY HEALTH UNITED GOVTECH Compulsory to use TraceTogether to check in at venues such as malls, schools, workplaces by December: Govt'.
text:
Not long now! 

By December, it will be compulsory to use the TraceTogether mobile application or token to check in at venues such as workplaces, schools, malls as well as food and beverage outlets under the Government's plan to further reopen the economy.

At these venues, people will not be able to check in by scanning their identification cards or SafeEntry QR codes with their phones, the Smart Nation and Digital Government Office said in a statement yesterday.

Instead, they will have to either use the TraceTogether app to scan a QR code at the premises or have the staff there scan the QR code found on their token.

Currently, only the use of SafeEntry is compulsory.

Read on, when you click on the link in bio @todayonline 

#trace #tracker #tracetogether #covid_19 #corona #covid #government #sg #app

image_desc: Photo by KiKi Mae in Buona Vista Community Club.
text:
Ok I got it, now what? #tracetogether #tracetogethertoken #tracetogetherapp

2. How does the token work?

Users can carry the TraceTogether token in a bag or in their pocket, since it is a small device.

The token exchanges short-distance Bluetooth signals with nearby tokens or handsets that have the TraceTogether app, and this interaction is logged into the devices.

All logs are encrypted and logs older than 25 days will be automatically erased.

If the user becomes infected with Covid-19, the device will need to be physically handed over to the authorities to extract the data needed for contact tracing.

text:
我国将逐步强制更多场所使用“合力追踪”来登记访客。除了电影院之外，人们日后前往工作场所、学校、购物中心、餐饮场所，或出席现场表演时，也必须使用“合力追踪”应用或携手防疫器。

image_desc: Photo shared by Coconuts Singapore on October 19, 2020 tagging @theprojectorsg. May be an image of text that says 'Singapore moviegoers are required to use COVID tracking app or device before entering theatres from Monday onwards SG UNITED COCONUTS'.
text:
Singapore will require all moviegoers to use a tracking app or device to check into theatres before entry starting Monday. 

It is an additional step for Singaporeans, who in recent months have been logging their whereabouts as part of coronavirus contact-tracing measures by either scanning identification cards or using the SafeEntry digital check-in system on their phones. But that will no longer do at movie theatres starting Monday. 

Independent movie theatre The Projector yesterday was the first to announce the new measure. It said that it, along with other cinema operators, had been ordered to implement the new measures soon. They were granted a grace period up to Nov. 16 to implement the new requirements.

“Starting 26th October (that’s next week!) the government has hereby decreed that everyone must use the TraceTogether App OR Token for Safe Entry to all cinemas in Singapore. You will NOT be allowed entry if you do not use either the TraceTogether app or [TraceTogether] Token for SafeEntry into our cinema. Please go and download the app now!” the cinema said yesterday.
Read more (LINK IN BIO)!
.

.

text:
Reposted from @theprojectorsg IMPORTANT! PLEASE READ! 

We have a Together and Trace plan… We have a TraceTogether.  We care at The Projector. 
 
Starting 26th October (that's next week!) the government has hereby decreed that everyone must use the TraceTogether App OR Token for Safe Entry to all cinemas in Singapore. This means our Safe Entry QR codes will no longer be compatible with Singpass, QR Code Scanner, or your Camera App. Never fear, you can download the TraceTogether App from the App Store/Google Play Store!

You will NOT be allowed entry if you do not use either the TraceTogether app or TraceToegether Token for SafeEntry into our cinema. Please go and download the app now!

If you do not have an app-enabled phone, find out where to collect a TraceTogether token here:  token.gowhere.gov.sg

For anyone who does not cooperate...don't blame us when Turkish Luke Skywalker comes for you…don’t say we never give chance.
